{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 4b shows the architecture of our proposed multichannels prototypical network.Specifically, we first initialize (N + 1) prototype vectors with 0.",
    "Then, to build multichannels setting, each prototype vectors p c and each token representation h i need to be split into m vectors from the dimension level, as follows:P = { p 0, p 1,..., p c }, c = 0, 1,..., N(6)p c = { p 1 c | p 2 c |... | p m c }(7)h i = { h 1 i | h 2 i |... | h m i }(8)Here, { | } denotes the split operation on the dimension and m is the number of multichannels.",
    "Then, for each prototype sub-vector p k c of a specific event label, we use token feature sub-representation h k i of specific label to fill.",
    "Finally, the m prototypes of each class are aggregated into a unified feature space, as follows:p k c = ι |S c | i∈S (c) h k i (9) p c = { p 1 c p 2 c... p m c }(10)where the dimension of p k c and h k i are both R (d h /m).",
    "the ι is a scalar temperature and {; } denotes the concatenation operation on the dimension."
  ]
}